    <div class="container">
        <h1>SPLICE Won't Open?</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Extension installed but not showing in Premiere Pro? Here's the fix.</p>

        <div class="critical">
            <div class="critical-title">Most Common Issue: Debug Mode Not Enabled</div>
            <p style="color: #d1d5db; line-height: 1.6;">
                Adobe Premiere Pro blocks unsigned CEP extensions by default. You need to enable CEP debug mode to allow SPLICE to run.
                This is a <strong>one-time setup</strong> and only takes 30 seconds.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fix-section">
            <div class="fix-title">üîß Quick Fix (macOS)</div>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Open <strong>Terminal</strong> (press Cmd+Space, type "terminal", hit Enter)</li>
                <li>Copy and paste this command, then press Enter:
                    <div class="command-box">defaults write com.adobe.CSXS.11 PlayerDebugMode 1</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Completely quit</strong> Premiere Pro (Cmd+Q, don't just close the window)
                </li>
                <li>Reopen Premiere Pro</li>
                <li>Go to <span class="code">Window ‚Üí Extensions ‚Üí SPLICE - AI Video Editor</span></li>
            </ol>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>Still not working?</strong> Try CSXS.12 or CSXS.13 depending on your Premiere Pro version:
                <div class="command-box">defaults write com.adobe.CSXS.12 PlayerDebugMode 1</div>
                <div class="command-box">defaults write com.adobe.CSXS.13 PlayerDebugMode 1</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fix-section">
            <div class="fix-title">üîß Quick Fix (Windows)</div>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Press <strong>Windows Key + R</strong> to open Run dialog</li>
                <li>Type <span class="code">regedit</span> and press Enter</li>
                <li>Navigate to:
                    <div class="command-box">HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Adobe\CSXS.11</div>
                </li>
                <li>Right-click in the right pane ‚Üí <strong>New ‚Üí String Value</strong></li>
                <li>Name it: <span class="code">PlayerDebugMode</span></li>
                <li>Double-click it and set value to: <span class="code">1</span></li>
                <li><strong>Completely quit</strong> Premiere Pro (don't just close the window)</li>
                <li>Reopen Premiere Pro</li>
                <li>Go to <span class="code">Window ‚Üí Extensions ‚Üí SPLICE - AI Video Editor</span></li>
            </ol>

            <div class="warning">
                <strong>Still not working?</strong> Try CSXS.12 or CSXS.13 registry keys instead of CSXS.11
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="success-check">
            <h3>‚úÖ How to Verify It Worked</h3>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Open Premiere Pro</li>
                <li>Click <span class="code">Window</span> in the menu bar</li>
                <li>Hover over <span class="code">Extensions</span></li>
                <li>You should see <strong>"SPLICE - AI Video Editor"</strong> in the list</li>
                <li>Click it - the panel should open on the right side</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="fix-section">
            <div class="fix-title">üîç Other Common Issues</div>

            <h4 style="color: #00D4FF; margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">Issue: Extension shows in menu but won't open</h4>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Quit Premiere Pro completely</li>
                <li>Delete CEP cache:
                    <div class="command-box">~/Library/Caches/Adobe/CEP (macOS)</div>
                    <div class="command-box">%APPDATA%\Adobe\CEP (Windows)</div>
                </li>
                <li>Restart Premiere Pro</li>
            </ol>

            <h4 style="color: #00D4FF; margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">Issue: "Extension is not compatible"</h4>
            <p style="color: #d1d5db; margin: 10px 0;">
                Make sure you're using <strong>Premiere Pro 2024 or newer</strong> (version 24.0+).
                SPLICE requires Premiere Pro 2024 minimum.
            </p>

            <h4 style="color: #00D4FF; margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">Issue: Panel opens but is blank/white</h4>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Right-click inside the blank panel</li>
                <li>Click <strong>"Inspect Element"</strong> to open debug console</li>
                <li>Look for red errors in the Console tab</li>
                <li>Take a screenshot and send to support</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="critical">
            <div class="critical-title">Still Need Help?</div>
            <p style="color: #d1d5db; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                If none of these solutions work:
            </p>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li>Open Chrome and go to <span class="code">http://localhost:8092</span></li>
                <li>Click on <strong>"SPLICE"</strong> in the list</li>
                <li>Take a screenshot of any errors you see</li>
                <li>Send screenshot to support along with:
                    <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                        <li>Your Premiere Pro version (Help ‚Üí About)</li>
                        <li>Your macOS/Windows version</li>
                        <li>Whether debug mode command ran successfully</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            SPLICE v6.0.5 Troubleshooting Guide<br>
            Updated: January 12, 2026
        </div>
    </div>
